Members of a mob that attacked and killed Abongile Mafalala will appear in court. Mafalala was killed in Parkwood on the Cape Flats after being wrongly identified as a kidnapper. eNCA/Nobesuthu Hejana Liquor traders in Cape Town say the Western Caoe government is being unreasonable and playing sides. Tavern owners have been slapped with heavy fines albeit being fully licensed and having proper documentation. eNCA/Ronald Masinda Members of a mob that attacked and killed Abongile Mafalala will appear in court. Mafalala was killed in Parkwood on the Cape Flats after being wrongly identified as a kidnapper. eNCA/Nobesuthu Hejana Liquor traders in Cape Town say the Western Caoe government is being unreasonable and playing sides. Tavern owners have been slapped with heavy fines albeit being fully licensed and having proper documentation. eNCA/Ronald Masinda Members of a mob that attacked and killed Abongile Mafalala will appear in court. Mafalala was killed in Parkwood on the Cape Flats after being wrongly identified as a kidnapper. eNCA/Nobesuthu Hejana Liquor traders in Cape Town say the Western Caoe government is being unreasonable and playing sides. Tavern owners have been slapped with heavy fines albeit being fully licensed and having proper documentation. eNCA/Ronald Masinda